,'','2017-01-09 19:24:52','2017-01-09 13:54:52','',218,'http://amitayu.com/218-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(225,1,'2017-01-09 19:29:05','2017-01-09 13:59:05','<strong>Herping</strong> is the act of searching for amphibians or reptiles for recreational, scientific or social reasons.\r\n\r\nMany techniques are used when a person goes herping. One popular technique is known as road running, road cruising or cruising. This is done by riding in a vehicle and traveling down stretches of road at a slow speed to count or catch animals. There are high chances of finding reptiles or amphibians basking in the sun during the early morning or just after a rainstorm.\r\n\r\nThe second technique is searching under natural cover objects (such as rocks and logs) and artificial cover objects (such as trash or construction debris), sometimes called \'<strong>flipping</strong>\'. It is ethical to keep the flipped object in its original position after searching beneath it.\r\n\r\nOther techniques to search for toads, snakes, caecilians or frogs involve looking inside nooks and corners of tree trunks, searching for <strong>camouflaged</strong> species on barks of trees or specific foliage, looking for species resting in shrubs of particular height and scrutinizing the area near water sources. In India, during the monsoon season, reptiles and amphibians become extremely active as it is the breeding season. If one studies the habitat well, it is not very difficult to spot one.\r\n\r\nBut like birding, herping depends totally on the herper\'s luck.\r\n\r\nHere are some of the places for beginners to start from.','Herping','','inherit','closed','closed','','218-revision-v1','','','2017-01-09 19:29:05','2017-01-09 13:59:05','',218,'http://amitayu.com/218-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(226,1,'2017-01-09 19:37:53','2017-01-09 14:07:53','Birding, or bird watching, is the recreational hobby of observing species of wild birds, including their physical characteristics and behavior. In reality, birding is much more than a simple hobby and there are many benefits of birding that can be enjoyed by both novice and experienced birders.\n\n&nbsp;It can be done with the naked eye, through a visual enhancement device like binoculars or by listening for bird sounds.\n\nAs birders observe new species, they not only learn about different birds, but they also learn about migration, bird behavior, feed preferences, courtship and bird territories.\n\nBirding is great exercise for all fitness levels. Observing many different species of birds may require long hikes and walks over uneven and challenging terrain while carrying a field bag with guides, binoculars, scopes and other equipment. Even backyard birders get fabulous exercise as they heft large bags of seed, clean feeders and keep up landscaping to benefit wild birds.\n\nConscientious birders practice sound wildlife habitat conservation habits to keep birds healthy, including reducing or eliminating chemical pesticides and fertilizers on their lawns.\n\nAll it takes to get started as a birder is good eyesight, a simple field guide (even from a used book store) and an interest in watching birds. For an enthusiastic birder, nothing is more exciting than spotting a new or rare bird, or learning to distinguish individual birds through their personalities. The fresh air along a birding trail can be invigorating, while the companionship of backyard birds can brighten any dreary day.\n\nHere are a few destinations for beginners.','Birding','','inherit','closed','closed','','216-autosave-v1','','','2017-01-09 19:37:53','2017-01-09 14:07:53','',216,'http://amitayu.com/216-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(227,1,'2017-01-09 19:38:33','2017-01-09 14:08:33','<strong>Birding</strong>, or bird watching, is the recreational hobby of observing species of wild birds, including their physical characteristics and behavior. In reality, birding is much more than a simple hobby and there are many benefits of birding that can be enjo