ies. The trails around the resort being not so fruitful, we stuck to the main birding area. Not only did several species grace us with their presence, ample photographic opportunities were also provided to us.\r\nIn the afternoon, we took a walk around the Supa dam. The sun was scorching but the breeze from the river cooled us down. We spotted Malabar giant squirrels at every alternate tree. We had to rush back on time for the main birding show. We could not afford to miss that for anything.\r\nOn the third day, we took the same road which led to the dam for the morning trail, the last trail of the trip. The following birds were seen  Orange minivet, flowerpecker, <strong>FILL</strong>.\r\nAfter breakfast we checked out and left the resort to reach Londa for our train.\r\nThe two nights and three days trip went by in a jiffy and we were already looking forward to the next trip. Whew what a trip!!\r\nClick <strong>here</strong> to have a look at the list of birds and other animals.','Ganeshgudi 2014','','inherit','closed','closed','','66-revision-v1','','','2017-01-13 19:49:31','2017-01-13 14:19:31','',66,'http://amitayu.com/66-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(237,1,'2017-01-13 19:52:30','2017-01-13 14:22:30','<strong>Ganeshgudi</strong> trip was planned on the spur of a moment. I happened to browse through the website of <strong>Old Magazine House</strong> (OMH) one fine evening and went through the tariff and the reservation page (it was purely coincidental). The availability of a cottage was making me very uncomfortable but convincing the wife to take a leave at such a short notice seemed a herculean task. Luckily God has bestowed us with sick leaves. So after a few days, on the 14th of March, 2014, in the wee hours of the morning, we boarded a train from Pune.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"img-responsive wp-image-10 size-large alignleft\" src=\"http://amitayu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Green_Vine_Snake-1024x509.jpg\" width=\"720\" height=\"358\">\r\n\r\n<strong>How to